						<div class="postbody">Of course, the problem with drawing with roughly screen-sized chunks, such as your 256x256, is that it makes the maps more repetitive. In fact, some sections in 1-1 of Super Mario Land for Game Boy were so repetitive that the first time I played, I thought I was in a looping level similar to 4-4 and 7-4 of the original Super Mario Bros. I think that's why Sonic 2 for Genesis used chunks no larger than 128x128.</div>

